<paragraph id="422DA15AFF94FF9AFF3DFBF5FB3FE5B2" blockId="1.[151,1437,1108,1493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF94FF9AFF3DFBF5FF6CE507" bold="true" box="[151,218,1108,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Notes</emphasis>
. With now 115 species, 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF94FF9AFE5AFBF5FDE4E507" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1898" box="[496,594,1108,1133]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Belisana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF94FF9AFE5AFBF5FDE4E507" box="[496,594,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Belisana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the second most species rich genus in 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF94FF9AFB8DFBF5FF6DE5FA" authority="(World Spider Catalog 2018)" authorityName="World Spider Catalog" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="World Spider Catalog" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Pholcidae (
<bibRefCitation id="2603DCABFF94FF9AFB0FFBF5FF62E5FA" author="World Spider Catalog" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref29006" refString="World Spider Catalog (2018) World Spider Catalog. Fersion 19.0. Natural History Museum Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 16 April 2018)" type="url" year="2018">World Spider Catalog 2018</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. It is highly diverse in Southeast Asia, but ranges from 
<collectingCountry id="3A85E1CAFF94FF9AFCFFFBD6FC39E5FA" box="[853,911,1143,1168]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="3A85E1CAFF94FF9AFC6DFBD6FB83E5FA" box="[967,1077,1143,1168]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
in the west to 
<collectingCountry id="3A85E1CAFF94FF9AFB75FBD9FAA9E5E5" box="[1247,1311,1144,1167]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="3A85E1CAFF94FF9AFAFDFBD6FAC8E5FA" box="[1367,1406,1143,1168]" name="Fiji" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fiji</collectingCountry>
in the east (Huber 2005). Morphology and molecular data suggest that the isolated African â€˜ 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF94FF9AFB29FB3DFAADE5DF" authorityName="Hentz" authorityYear="1841" box="[1155,1307,1180,1205]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Spermophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF94FF9AFB29FB3DFAADE5DF" box="[1155,1307,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Spermophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
â€™ 
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF94FF9AFA86FB3DFA2AE5DF" box="[1324,1436,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">kyambura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2603DCABFF94FF9AFF3DFB1EFE3CE5B2" author="Huber, B. A." box="[151,394,1215,1240]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref27136" refString="Huber, B. A. (2012) Revision and cladistic analysis of the Afrotropical endemic genus Smeringopus Simon, 1890 (Araneae: Pholcidae). Zootaxa, 3461, 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="2012">
Huber &amp; Warui, 
<date id="362C879AFF94FF9AFEF8FB61FE3CE5B2" box="[338,394,1216,1240]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2012-05">2012</date>
</bibRefCitation>
may also belong to 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF94FF9AFDC6FB1EFD78E5B2" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1898" box="[620,718,1215,1240]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Belisana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF94FF9AFDC6FB1EFD78E5B2" box="[620,718,1215,1240]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Belisana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2603DCABFF94FF9AFD77FB1EFC1FE5B2" author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." box="[733,937,1215,1240]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="141" refId="ref26630" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
